WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.150
Welcome. If you're here, that means you've
already put in work. You know the

2
00:00:05.200 --> 00:00:10.650
framework, listen, acknowledge, ask,
redirect, and you've seen

3
00:00:10.700 --> 00:00:12.190
the most common objections.

4
00:00:12.520 --> 00:00:16.210
This lesson is where it becomes muscle
memory. We're going to drill real

5
00:00:16.260 --> 00:00:18.350
objections, one after another.

6
00:00:18.420 --> 00:00:22.850
The exact lines sellers throw at you on
real calls. Here's the honest truth

7
00:00:22.900 --> 00:00:27.330
about objection practice. You're not going
to walk away from one watch with all

8
00:00:27.380 --> 00:00:31.370
of this locked in. That's not how it
works, and that's not the expectation.

9
00:00:31.500 --> 00:00:33.450
What we want is reps.

10
00:00:33.760 --> 00:00:38.590
Every objection you drill here makes the
real one easier to hear, and every time

11
00:00:38.640 --> 00:00:42.730
one shows up on a call, you'll handle it a
little better than the last time.

12
00:00:43.080 --> 00:00:46.970
Here's how each drill works. A seller
throws the objection.

13
00:00:47.140 --> 00:00:52.250
You take a beat, your turn, and think
about how you'd handle it. Then I'll give

14
00:00:52.300 --> 00:00:55.590
you the line I'd use, so you can compare
it against yours.

15
00:00:55.800 --> 00:00:57.390
Ready for a first objection?

16
00:00:57.920 --> 00:01:03.030
First up, price. This is when a seller
pushes back on the number, they want

17
00:01:03.080 --> 00:01:05.850
more, or they want you to name yours
first.

18
00:01:07.180 --> 00:01:08.550
I want more money.

19
00:01:32.520 --> 00:01:36.810
I think we are probably capped, but I can
see if there is room.

20
00:01:36.940 --> 00:01:41.190
But before I do that, are you ready to
sign and move forward today?

21
00:01:41.580 --> 00:01:43.350
You give your price first.

22
00:02:06.900 --> 00:02:08.990
You really don't want my number yet.

23
00:02:09.040 --> 00:02:13.470
If I lead, you'll just shop it and kick me
out before I even see the house.

24
00:02:13.600 --> 00:02:17.510
Since you know it best, where would you
like to be so I can see if I can come up

25
00:02:17.560 --> 00:02:22.770
toward it? If you truly don't know,
imagine you did know, what would that look

26
00:02:22.820 --> 00:02:28.110
like? Or think Craigslist. You wouldn't
list a car for $0 and

27
00:02:28.160 --> 00:02:32.970
say, make me an offer. Give me your start
high number so I know the target.

28
00:02:33.300 --> 00:02:36.650
I need to net my number in my pocket after
everything.

29
00:02:58.860 --> 00:03:02.430
Understood. Let's reverse engineer it.

30
00:03:02.700 --> 00:03:07.230
If that's your walkaway number, we can get
there two ways.

31
00:03:07.540 --> 00:03:12.950
A lower cash price with zero fees and
speed, or closer to

32
00:03:13.000 --> 00:03:14.290
your number on terms.

33
00:03:14.580 --> 00:03:19.590
If I can guarantee your net without you
lifting a finger, which lane do you

34
00:03:19.640 --> 00:03:22.330
prefer? Cash or terms?

35
00:03:22.680 --> 00:03:25.670
I only want cash, no contingencies.

36
00:03:48.100 --> 00:03:53.270
Got it. I can bring a clean cash number
with a short timeline and no

37
00:03:53.320 --> 00:03:58.510
repair requests. The only box we have to
check is clear title so funds are

38
00:03:58.560 --> 00:04:00.030
safe and you're protected.

39
00:04:00.240 --> 00:04:05.210
If I make it simple and certain on your
schedule, are we good?

40
00:04:05.640 --> 00:04:07.450
Next, competition.

41
00:04:07.740 --> 00:04:12.770
These come up when the seller's shopping
around, talking to other investors, or

42
00:04:12.820 --> 00:04:14.110
thinking about listing.

43
00:04:15.260 --> 00:04:17.290
I'm going to list it with an agent.

44
00:04:40.820 --> 00:04:45.770
That can be a great path if you've got
time and the house is list ready. If you

45
00:04:45.820 --> 00:04:50.930
want speed and convenience, I'm your cash
or terms lane. Which matters more

46
00:04:50.980 --> 00:04:55.850
right now, highest possible price or
certainty and timeline?

47
00:04:56.380 --> 00:05:00.030
If price wins, I can often meet it with
terms.

48
00:05:00.360 --> 00:05:04.590
If speed wins, I'll keep it simple and
certain.

49
00:05:05.160 --> 00:05:07.910
I'm talking to other investors.

50
00:05:30.100 --> 00:05:35.390
No problem. What has to happen before
selling makes sense? When

51
00:05:35.440 --> 00:05:40.710
that happens, do you want me to bring a
clean cash option, a terms option

52
00:05:40.760 --> 00:05:45.310
that gets you closer to your price, or
both so you've got a simple choice?

53
00:05:45.660 --> 00:05:49.110
We're doing highest and best in investor
open house.

54
00:06:10.980 --> 00:06:14.110
I'm probably not your buyer for a bidding
circus.

55
00:06:14.460 --> 00:06:17.090
I'm the certain no-drama lane.

56
00:06:17.220 --> 00:06:21.030
If that route doesn't deliver what you
want, I'll be here with a clean number

57
00:06:21.080 --> 00:06:24.570
and performance. I've got it taken care of
already.

58
00:06:47.860 --> 00:06:53.230
Good to hear. Out of curiosity, what path
did you choose, and what would

59
00:06:53.280 --> 00:06:54.250
make it even better?

60
00:06:54.440 --> 00:06:59.690
If there's a gap on timing, certainty, or
hassle, I can fill it without blowing

61
00:06:59.740 --> 00:07:02.950
up your plan. I'm going to rent it
instead.

62
00:07:26.020 --> 00:07:31.170
That can work if you're prepared for
vacancies, repairs, and

63
00:07:31.220 --> 00:07:36.530
collections. If a tenant misses a month,
are you set to float it and

64
00:07:36.580 --> 00:07:41.970
handle the calls? If not, I can turn this
into mailbox money for you without

65
00:07:42.020 --> 00:07:47.530
landlording, by buying on terms at your
price and making the payment painless.

66
00:07:47.840 --> 00:07:53.230
Now, delay. This is the seller who wants
to slow things down, they need

67
00:07:53.280 --> 00:07:55.990
time, or they want to talk to someone
first.

68
00:07:57.280 --> 00:08:00.390
I'll get back to you after I talk to my
spouse.

69
00:08:22.440 --> 00:08:27.750
Absolutely. When do you two usually
connect? I'll text a simple summary

70
00:08:27.800 --> 00:08:29.650
so it's easy to review together.

71
00:08:29.780 --> 00:08:33.470
Then we can confirm what fits after you've
both looked it over.

72
00:08:33.740 --> 00:08:36.670
I can't sell right now. I need more time.

73
00:08:59.060 --> 00:09:01.470
I get it. No rush at all.

74
00:09:01.600 --> 00:09:03.230
When's a good time to chat again?

75
00:09:03.380 --> 00:09:06.190
I can answer more questions at that time
if you want.

76
00:09:06.460 --> 00:09:07.790
I'm too busy.

77
00:09:32.040 --> 00:09:35.050
Totally fair. Let's make this painless.

78
00:09:35.280 --> 00:09:39.390
Do you want me to bring you a simple cash
number with no showings and a quick

79
00:09:39.440 --> 00:09:44.190
close? Or a terms option that gets you
closer to your price without you lifting

80
00:09:44.240 --> 00:09:46.830
a finger? I need to think about it.

81
00:10:10.840 --> 00:10:15.910
Absolutely. It's a big decision, and I'd
never want you to feel rushed.

82
00:10:16.060 --> 00:10:18.810
Can I ask what specifically you're
weighing?

83
00:10:18.920 --> 00:10:22.230
I might be able to give you some more
information that helps.

84
00:10:22.820 --> 00:10:27.290
Let's talk trust. These are the moments a
seller isn't sure who you are, or

85
00:10:27.340 --> 00:10:29.721
whether they can believe what you're
telling them.

86
00:10:30.860 --> 00:10:32.390
What's your company name?

87
00:10:56.300 --> 00:11:01.590
Happy to share? We are a partnership, and
we close with a local title company,

88
00:11:01.680 --> 00:11:03.630
so everything's transparent.

89
00:11:03.980 --> 00:11:08.010
Do you prefer I email you a quick
one-pager with our info?

90
00:11:08.220 --> 00:11:10.010
Do you have proof of funds?

91
00:11:33.620 --> 00:11:38.050
Yes. I can send current proof of funds and
a couple of recent settlement

92
00:11:38.100 --> 00:11:41.070
statements, so you can see we actually
close.

93
00:11:41.300 --> 00:11:44.210
We'll keep it simple and verifiable
through title.

94
00:11:44.560 --> 00:11:46.130
How did you get my number?

95
00:12:09.860 --> 00:12:12.610
Public records and standard outreach.

96
00:12:12.820 --> 00:12:18.090
If you prefer text or email going forward,
I'm good with that. Is the property

97
00:12:18.140 --> 00:12:21.750
something you're open to selling if the
timing and terms make sense?

98
00:12:22.080 --> 00:12:24.430
I want my attorney to review it.

99
00:12:47.360 --> 00:12:52.670
I would encourage you to. There are
attorneys at the title company as well.

100
00:12:52.760 --> 00:12:55.170
They can answer questions for you too.

101
00:12:55.620 --> 00:12:59.690
If this is such a good deal, why don't you
buy it yourself?

102
00:13:20.800 --> 00:13:24.690
Fair question. I do buy a lot when it fits
my portfolio.

103
00:13:24.900 --> 00:13:27.790
And when it doesn't, I still solve the
problem.

104
00:13:27.980 --> 00:13:30.570
Sometimes I keep it. Sometimes I partner.

105
00:13:30.760 --> 00:13:33.170
Sometimes I place it with someone on my
team.

106
00:13:33.380 --> 00:13:37.690
Either way, you get a clean, certain
outcome without games.

107
00:13:37.960 --> 00:13:39.670
What matters more to you?

108
00:13:39.780 --> 00:13:42.490
Speed or squeezing every last dollar?

109
00:13:42.820 --> 00:13:44.470
Are you wholesaling this?

110
00:14:07.900 --> 00:14:12.150
I place deals in a few lanes. Sometimes I
buy.

111
00:14:12.380 --> 00:14:14.190
Sometimes I keep it as a rental.

112
00:14:14.380 --> 00:14:18.010
And sometimes I assign it to a partner
who's the better fit.

113
00:14:18.200 --> 00:14:23.150
Regardless of the lane, your price,
timeline, and certainty don't change.

114
00:14:23.400 --> 00:14:27.550
Do you care who's on the other side of the
table if you get the exact outcome we

115
00:14:27.600 --> 00:14:31.210
agree on? I'm worried you'll retrade me
after the inspection.

116
00:14:54.240 --> 00:14:57.090
Same page. I don't play that game.

117
00:14:57.140 --> 00:14:59.630
I give a number I can actually close on.

118
00:14:59.680 --> 00:15:04.470
And if something truly major comes up that
neither of us knew about, we either

119
00:15:04.520 --> 00:15:08.750
talk like adults or I release you cleanly
so you can move on.

120
00:15:09.260 --> 00:15:11.870
Certainty over games. Fair?

121
00:15:12.120 --> 00:15:15.550
I don't trust creative financing or terms.

122
00:15:37.760 --> 00:15:42.470
Totally fair. Most folks haven't had it
explained clearly.

123
00:15:42.800 --> 00:15:47.490
Terms just means we can trade flexibility
for price, payment,

124
00:15:47.780 --> 00:15:53.210
interest, or timeline. So you get what you
want without drama. If I can hit your

125
00:15:53.260 --> 00:15:58.030
price and make the monthly painless while
we close at a local title company,

126
00:15:58.140 --> 00:15:59.890
does that ease the concern?

127
00:16:00.140 --> 00:16:02.550
I don't want people knowing my business.

128
00:16:02.700 --> 00:16:03.830
Keep it private.

129
00:16:25.680 --> 00:16:28.930
Understood. We'll keep it fully
off-market.

130
00:16:29.120 --> 00:16:34.530
No signs, no photos online, one discreet
walkthrough, and we

131
00:16:34.580 --> 00:16:36.610
close through a local title company.

132
00:16:36.780 --> 00:16:39.570
Only the people who need to know are
involved.

133
00:16:39.700 --> 00:16:44.170
If privacy stays intact and the numbers
work, are you comfortable moving

134
00:16:44.220 --> 00:16:46.690
forward? I'm not interested.

135
00:17:11.420 --> 00:17:12.610
Completely understand.

136
00:17:13.240 --> 00:17:17.750
Before I let you go, is there a reason you
responded to our outreach in the

137
00:17:17.800 --> 00:17:22.550
first place? Sometimes things change over
time, and I just want to make sure we

138
00:17:22.600 --> 00:17:23.970
haven't missed something.

139
00:17:24.620 --> 00:17:29.650
Now, as is. These are about the house
itself, repairs,

140
00:17:29.880 --> 00:17:32.370
condition, and who deals with the work.

141
00:17:33.540 --> 00:17:35.330
I'll fix it myself.

142
00:17:58.820 --> 00:18:04.250
Make sense if time, cash, and contractors
line up.

143
00:18:04.520 --> 00:18:07.670
What's the budget and timeline you're
expecting.

144
00:18:07.840 --> 00:18:12.790
If you're over that by even a little, I
can trade you convenience for price and

145
00:18:12.840 --> 00:18:14.690
keep you out of contractor roulette.

146
00:18:14.740 --> 00:18:18.050
You go first on the walkthrough, then I'll
decide.

147
00:18:40.560 --> 00:18:43.590
Totally fine. Quick heads up though.

148
00:18:43.740 --> 00:18:47.750
If I lead before I see everything, you'll
just shop my number.

149
00:18:48.040 --> 00:18:52.510
Since you know the house best, where would
you like to be so I can see if I can

150
00:18:52.560 --> 00:18:57.710
come up toward it? If you truly don't
know, give me your start high number so I

151
00:18:57.760 --> 00:19:01.390
know the target. Then I'll confirm it
after a quick walk.

152
00:19:01.580 --> 00:19:04.230
I don't want to deal with repairs or
inspections.

153
00:19:26.740 --> 00:19:28.250
You won't have to.

154
00:19:28.380 --> 00:19:31.650
I buy as is and keep it simple.

155
00:19:32.040 --> 00:19:33.850
One quick walkthrough for photos.

156
00:19:34.040 --> 00:19:35.630
So I know what I'm buying.

157
00:19:35.760 --> 00:19:38.550
No punch lists. No nickel and diming.

158
00:19:38.620 --> 00:19:43.390
If something major pops up we didn't know
about, we talk like adults or I

159
00:19:43.440 --> 00:19:44.810
release you cleanly.

160
00:19:45.000 --> 00:19:46.630
Certainty over drama.

161
00:19:46.860 --> 00:19:50.590
Fair? Send your best offer by email or
text.

162
00:19:50.720 --> 00:19:52.310
I don't want to talk.

163
00:20:12.900 --> 00:20:14.910
I can send a clean number.

164
00:20:15.180 --> 00:20:16.530
Quick heads up though.

165
00:20:16.780 --> 00:20:22.050
If I shoot blind without two minutes of
context, I'll either overbid or

166
00:20:22.100 --> 00:20:27.330
underbid and waste your time. Give me
condition, timing, and what you need to

167
00:20:27.380 --> 00:20:31.710
walk away with. And I'll send my best in
writing and keep it straightforward.

168
00:20:32.300 --> 00:20:34.430
And finally, distress.

169
00:20:34.880 --> 00:20:36.430
The hardest spots?

170
00:20:36.940 --> 00:20:39.010
Foreclosure. Underwater?

171
00:20:39.240 --> 00:20:40.590
Behind on payments?

172
00:20:40.820 --> 00:20:43.550
Where you're really there to solve a
problem.

173
00:20:44.840 --> 00:20:46.270
I don't know what I owe.

174
00:21:13.400 --> 00:21:15.010
So we have exact numbers.

175
00:21:15.640 --> 00:21:18.070
Ballpark? Do you think you're above water?

176
00:21:18.120 --> 00:21:20.370
At break even? Or a little short?

177
00:21:20.460 --> 00:21:25.510
Once we see the payoff, I'll bring you a
cash option and a terms option so you

178
00:21:25.560 --> 00:21:26.830
can choose what fits.

179
00:21:27.040 --> 00:21:28.690
I can't get rid of my tenants.

180
00:21:51.660 --> 00:21:56.830
It happens a lot. I buy with occupants in
place

181
00:21:56.880 --> 00:21:59.070
and take the problem off your plate.

182
00:21:59.120 --> 00:22:04.530
I'll handle cash for keys or the legal
process after closing so you

183
00:22:04.580 --> 00:22:09.730
don't have to. If I make this my headache
and keep you out of court, are you

184
00:22:09.780 --> 00:22:11.250
open to moving forward?

185
00:22:11.540 --> 00:22:14.090
I owe too much. I'm underwater.

186
00:22:53.700 --> 00:22:55.350
I'm in foreclosure.

187
00:22:55.960 --> 00:22:57.750
I don't think there's time.

188
00:23:19.180 --> 00:23:21.910
There's still a path if we move now.

189
00:23:22.100 --> 00:23:27.390
I can bring the loan current, stop the
sale, and take over payments so you can

190
00:23:27.440 --> 00:23:31.930
breathe again and rebuild your credit with
on-time pays showing up each month.

191
00:23:31.980 --> 00:23:36.670
If I handle the catch-up and line up your
move, is that the outcome you want?

192
00:23:36.900 --> 00:23:39.530
I need a lease back or I can't move yet.

193
00:24:02.920 --> 00:24:08.070
I can close, fund you, and let you stay
for an agreed period with a

194
00:24:08.120 --> 00:24:09.950
simple per-day use fee

195
00:24:11.640 --> 00:24:16.630
I feel safe and I feel safe. If I give you
certainty now and the time to move

196
00:24:16.680 --> 00:24:19.330
later, are we good to button this up?

197
00:24:19.520 --> 00:24:21.670
You just covered a lot of ground.

198
00:24:21.940 --> 00:24:26.650
Dozens of real objections that are going
to show up in your calls every single

199
00:24:26.700 --> 00:24:31.310
day. Here's what I want you to take with
you. You don't need a perfect answer

200
00:24:31.360 --> 00:24:33.150
memorized for every one of these.

201
00:24:33.200 --> 00:24:35.570
What you need is the framework.

202
00:24:35.740 --> 00:24:37.530
Listen. Acknowledge.

203
00:24:37.700 --> 00:24:42.990
Ask. Redirect. And enough reps that when a
seller pushes back, a bell goes

204
00:24:43.040 --> 00:24:46.310
off. That's when this training starts
doing its job.

205
00:24:46.480 --> 00:24:48.190
Come back to these drills.

206
00:24:48.560 --> 00:24:52.970
Rewatch the ones that didn't fully land
yet. That's not a sign you miss

207
00:24:53.020 --> 00:24:55.450
something. That's just how practice works.

208
00:24:55.500 --> 00:24:59.310
It sticks when you start hearing it in
real conversations.

209
00:24:59.620 --> 00:25:04.670
Next up, the complex stuff. The objections
that make most people on the phone

210
00:25:04.720 --> 00:25:06.870
freeze. You've got the foundation.

211
00:25:07.040 --> 00:25:08.310
Let's build on it.
